Subject: [PATCH] chore: post-Phase-0 review fixes
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four small fixes flagged during the deep review of the Phase 0
scaffolding. Single PR because each one is too small to stand alone.

1. Nested PII redaction
   redact_pii previously walked only top-level event_dict keys. A
   future call like log.info('indexed', activity={'gps_lat': ...})
   would leak. Added structural recursion into dicts, lists, and
   tuples up to depth 4 (enough for activity → laps → samples →
   field) and matching unit + integration tests. Nested caller
   objects are *not* mutated — the processor builds new dicts.

2. Disable uvicorn access logs
   Uvicorn's access logger writes via stdlib logging, bypassing the
   structlog PII chain. Once Phase 1 lands /oauth/callback?code=…
   those URL parameters would appear in cleartext on stdout. Both
   __main__.py entry points now pass uvicorn_config={'access_log':
   False} to FastMCP.run. /health still works; uvicorn lifecycle
   logs ('Started server process' etc.) still emit via
   uvicorn.error, which carries no user data.

3. __version__ from importlib.metadata
   All three __init__.py files now read __version__ via
   importlib.metadata.version(...) rather than hardcoding. Bumping
   the wheel version in pyproject.toml is now enough to update what
   /health reports — single source of truth.

4. Roadmap currency
   docs/roadmap.md 'Current state' said 'Phase 0 (not yet started)'.
   Flipped to 'Phase 0 complete; Phase 1 prerequisites pending',
   ticked the Phase 0 checkboxes, and set Last updated. CLAUDE.md
   tells future agents to trust the docs; this keeps them honest.

Local verification:
  pytest             49/49 passed
  mypy --strict      clean across all 3 packages
  ruff check         clean
  ruff format        clean
  python -m mcp_stryd → GET /health → 200, access log line absent

